Afrobeats singer, Tiwa Savage’s ex-husband, Tunji Balogun aka Teebillz has welcomed a son with his new lover. The talent manager announced the arrival of his son via his Instagram page where he shared a photo with his newborn while feeding him. The music executive captioned post: “Blessed to experience the most amazing feeling once again……..King Zayn.” TeeBillz also posted a video where he could be seen cuddling his son. He was seated on the sofa with his baby in his arms while he kept rubbing his little back. - Advertisement - He captioned video: “Amazing grace…King Zayn #Alhamdulillah.”   My ex-girlfriend had no twins for me, says Harrysong     Singer Slim Joe dies of kidney failure     Comedian Woli Arole, wife welcome baby boy   Read Also: SCANDALS OF THE YEAR: TIWA SAVAGE AND DCP ABBA KYARI Savage and Teebillz got married in 2013 in one of the most well-attended celebrity weddings of the decade. However, things took a different turn in 2016 after the couple went on social media to call each other out over infidelity. At midnight, sometime in April 2016, the “Somebody’s Son” granted an interview in which she declared that her less than two years marriage with former manager, TeeBillz, was over. She narrated her husband’s infidelity, wanton spending of her money and substance abuse. On his part, TeeBillz accused his wife of sleeping around with several of her colleagues. Their separation can be described as one of the messiest in the history of the Nigerian entertainment industry. They have a son together, Jamil Balogun.